African Rainbow Has Longest Streak of Gains Since September 2010 on Profit

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-08-31T07:05:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/african-rainbow-has-longest-streak-of-gains-since-september-2010-on-profit.html
African Rainbow Minerals Ltd. (ARI) , a
South African mining company, rose to the highest intraday level
in more than two weeks after saying full-year profit excluding
one-time items rose 94 percent.  The stock rallied for a sixth day, its longest streak of
gains since September 2010, adding 1.5 percent to 183.06 rand by
9:04 a.m. in Johannesburg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  